---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ReviewsSection from '../../components/ReviewsSection.astro';

const phone = '01623 325 123';
const telHref = `tel:${phone.replace(/\s+/g, '')}`;

// Repair coverage is calculated as straight-line distance from our HQ
// in Bilsthorpe (NG22 8GA) using postcodes.io for the customer's
// lat/lon. Adjust the radius if you want a tighter or looser zone.
// Coords are from postcodes.io for NG22 8GA (verified May 2026).
const repairOrigin = { lat: 53.136909, lon: -1.033037, label: 'Bilsthorpe (NG22)' };
// Reference distances from NG22 8GA (Haversine, postcodes.io coords):
//   Southwell ~5.5mi · Mansfield ~7.2mi · Newark ~10mi · Worksop ~12mi
//   Nottingham ~13.3mi · Retford ~13.4mi
const repairRadiusMiles = 8;

const serviceJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Service',
  name: 'Mobile Tyre Repair',
  serviceType: 'Mobile Tyre Puncture Repair',
  provider: {
    '@type': 'LocalBusiness',
    name: 'Tyre Emergency Ltd',
    telephone: '+441623325123',
    url: 'https://tyreemergencyltd.co.uk/',
  },
  areaServed: 'Nottinghamshire, East Midlands',
  description: 'On-site puncture repair carried out to British Standard AU159 across Nottinghamshire and the surrounding counties.',
  url: 'https://tyreemergencyltd.co.uk/services/mobile-tyre-repair/',
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Mobile Tyre Repair Nottinghamshire | BS AU159 Puncture Repair"
  description="Mobile puncture repair carried out to British Standard AU159 within ~10 miles of Bilsthorpe, Nottinghamshire. We bring a replacement tyre too, just in case, so you&rsquo;re not stuck. Call 01623 325 123."
  jsonLd={JSON.stringify(serviceJsonLd)}
>
  <section class="service-hero" style="background-image: url('/images/puncture-repair.webp');">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Repair Service</span>
      <h1>Mobile Tyre Repair</h1>
      <p class="service-intro">
        A puncture repair is the smart option when you&rsquo;ve still got plenty of life left in the tyre and don&rsquo;t want to throw money at a brand new one. We do them properly to British Standard AU159 &mdash; and if the damage means a repair isn&rsquo;t safe, we&rsquo;ve already brought a replacement tyre with us so you&rsquo;re not stuck.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-call" href={telHref}>
          <span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> Call: {phone}
        </a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="#repair-area-check">Check my postcode</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ReviewsSection />

  <section class="section section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-split">
        <div class="service-split-image">
          <img
            src="/images/puncture-repair.webp"
            alt="A Ford alloy wheel with a Bridgestone tyre ready to be inspected and repaired"
            width="1600"
            height="1200"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="service-split-content">
          <span class="eyebrow">A few things worth knowing</span>
          <h2>How we handle puncture repairs</h2>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li><strong>Within around 10 miles of Bilsthorpe (NG22)</strong> &mdash; puncture repairs are priced from &pound;50 upwards. Outside that radius the maths stops working for both of us, so we&rsquo;ll let you know on the call rather than waste your time.</li>
            <li><strong>We bring a replacement tyre too, just in case.</strong> Not every puncture is repairable &mdash; if it&rsquo;s in the sidewall, shoulder, or the tyre&rsquo;s below the limit, we&rsquo;ve already got a fresh one on the van so we don&rsquo;t leave you with an empty wheel.</li>
            <li><strong>Done to BS AU159</strong> &mdash; tyre off the rim, full inside inspection and a combined plug-and-patch from the inside, not a string-and-glue job stuck in from the outside.</li>
            <li><strong>Re-balanced after the repair</strong> on the mobile balancer, pressures set to the manufacturer&rsquo;s figure, TPMS reset if your vehicle uses sensors.</li>
            <li><strong>Honest call on whether it&rsquo;s worth repairing</strong> &mdash; if the tyre&rsquo;s near the end of its life anyway, we&rsquo;ll tell you straight rather than charge you for a repair that&rsquo;s only going to last weeks.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-darker">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">When You Need This</span>
      <h2>Typical repair jobs</h2>
      <div class="scenarios">
        <article class="scenario">
          <h3>Screw or nail in the tread</h3>
          <p>You&rsquo;ve spotted the head of a screw in the tyre or pulled one out and it&rsquo;s now going down. If it&rsquo;s in the central tread area, this is exactly the sort of puncture we can repair properly and give you years more out of the tyre.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="scenario">
          <h3>Slow puncture you keep topping up</h3>
          <p>You&rsquo;ve been pumping it up every few days and it&rsquo;s starting to get annoying. We&rsquo;ll get the tyre off, find the leak (often a tiny shard of glass) and tell you whether to repair it or replace it.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="scenario">
          <h3>Plenty of tread left, don&rsquo;t want to bin it</h3>
          <p>The tyre is fairly new, the tread is good, and you don&rsquo;t want to spend money on a fresh one if a proper repair will do. If it&rsquo;s safely repairable, that&rsquo;s the call we&rsquo;ll make.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="scenario">
          <h3>Pre-trip check before a long drive</h3>
          <p>Tyre&rsquo;s losing air slowly and you&rsquo;ve got a long journey coming up. We&rsquo;ll get it sorted on the driveway so you can leave without it nagging at the back of your mind.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-light service-cta-section" id="repair-area-check">
    <div class="container container-narrow text-center">
      <h2>Got a puncture? Check we cover you.</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-dark">
        Pop your postcode in below &mdash; we&rsquo;ll work out how far you are from us and tell you straight away whether you&rsquo;re inside our puncture repair zone.
      </p>

      <form class="postcode-check" id="repair-postcode-form" novalidate>
        <label class="visually-hidden" for="repair-postcode">Your postcode</label>
        <input
          id="repair-postcode"
          class="postcode-check-input"
          name="postcode"
          type="text"
          autocomplete="postal-code"
          inputmode="text"
          aria-describedby="repair-postcode-result"
          required
        />
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary postcode-check-submit" id="repair-postcode-submit">
          Check coverage
        </button>
      </form>

      <div
        id="repair-postcode-result"
        class="postcode-check-result"
        role="status"
        aria-live="polite"
        hidden
      ></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline define:vars={{ repairOrigin, repairRadiusMiles, phone, telHref }}>
    (function () {
      var form = document.getElementById('repair-postcode-form');
      var input = document.getElementById('repair-postcode');
      var submit = document.getElementById('repair-postcode-submit');
      var result = document.getElementById('repair-postcode-result');
      if (!form || !input || !submit || !result) return;

      // We need the full postcode (outward + inward) to look up an
      // accurate lat/lon. The outcode regex is only used to give a
      // more helpful error if someone enters just the first half.
      var POSTCODE_RE = /^([A-Z]{1,2}\d{1,2}[A-Z]?)\s*(\d[A-Z]{2})$/i;
      var OUTCODE_RE  = /^([A-Z]{1,2}\d{1,2}[A-Z]?)$/i;

      function escapeHtml(s) {
        return String(s).replace(/[&<>"']/g, function (c) {
          return ({ '&':'&amp;','<':'&lt;','>':'&gt;','"':'&quot;',"'":'&#39;' })[c];
        });
      }

      // Haversine distance in miles.
      function milesBetween(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2) {
        var R = 3958.8;
        var toRad = function (d) { return d * Math.PI / 180; };
        var dLat = toRad(lat2 - lat1);
        var dLon = toRad(lon2 - lon1);
        var a = Math.sin(dLat / 2) * Math.sin(dLat / 2)
              + Math.cos(toRad(lat1)) * Math.cos(toRad(lat2))
                * Math.sin(dLon / 2) * Math.sin(dLon / 2);
        return R * 2 * Math.atan2(Math.sqrt(a), Math.sqrt(1 - a));
      }

      function setBusy(busy) {
        submit.disabled = busy;
        submit.textContent = busy ? 'Checking…' : 'Check coverage';
      }

      function render(state, ctx) {
        ctx = ctx || {};
        result.hidden = false;
        result.className = 'postcode-check-result postcode-check-result--' + state;

        var label = escapeHtml(ctx.postcode || '');
        var dist = ctx.miles != null ? ctx.miles.toFixed(1) : null;

        if (state === 'covered') {
          result.innerHTML =
            '<p class="postcode-check-headline">' +
              'Yes &mdash; we cover <strong>' + label + '</strong> for puncture repair.' +
            '</p>' +
            '<p class="postcode-check-sub">' +
              'You&rsquo;re about <strong>' + dist + ' miles</strong> from us. Give us a ring with your reg and your location &mdash; if it&rsquo;s repairable, we will, and if it isn&rsquo;t, we&rsquo;ve got a replacement tyre with us so you&rsquo;re still going home today.' +
            '</p>' +
            '<a class="btn btn-primary btn-call postcode-check-cta" href="' + telHref + '">' +
              '<span aria-hidden="true">☎</span> Call ' + escapeHtml(phone) +
            '</a>';
        } else if (state === 'outside') {
          result.innerHTML =
            '<p class="postcode-check-headline">' +
              'Sorry &mdash; <strong>' + label + '</strong> is outside our puncture repair area.' +
            '</p>' +
            '<p class="postcode-check-sub">' +
              'You&rsquo;re about <strong>' + dist + ' miles</strong> from us, and we keep mobile repairs within roughly ' + repairRadiusMiles + ' miles of Bilsthorpe (NG22) to keep the price fair and the wait short. For a repair in your area you&rsquo;ll want to look at a local tyre shop or fitter who&rsquo;s set up to come to you.' +
            '</p>';
        } else if (state === 'notfound') {
          result.innerHTML =
            '<p class="postcode-check-headline postcode-check-headline--error">' +
              'We couldn&rsquo;t find that postcode &mdash; double-check the spelling and try again.' +
            '</p>';
        } else if (state === 'partial') {
          result.innerHTML =
            '<p class="postcode-check-headline postcode-check-headline--error">' +
              'We need the full postcode to work out the distance.' +
            '</p>' +
            '<p class="postcode-check-sub">' +
              'Add the second half (e.g. <strong>NG18 1AA</strong>, not just <strong>NG22</strong>) so we can give you an accurate answer.' +
            '</p>';
        } else if (state === 'network') {
          result.innerHTML =
            '<p class="postcode-check-headline postcode-check-headline--error">' +
              'Couldn&rsquo;t check that just now.' +
            '</p>' +
            '<p class="postcode-check-sub">' +
              'Give us a ring on <a href="' + telHref + '">' + escapeHtml(phone) + '</a> and we&rsquo;ll tell you straight away whether we cover you.' +
            '</p>';
        } else {
          result.innerHTML =
            '<p class="postcode-check-headline postcode-check-headline--error">' +
              'That doesn&rsquo;t look like a UK postcode. Try something like NG18 1AA.' +
            '</p>';
        }
      }

      form.addEventListener('submit', async function (e) {
        e.preventDefault();
        var raw = (input.value || '').trim().toUpperCase().replace(/\s+/g, ' ');
        if (!raw) { render('error'); return; }

        var fullMatch = raw.match(POSTCODE_RE);
        if (!fullMatch) {
          // Outcode-only ("NG22") gets a specific message; anything
          // else falls back to the generic "doesn't look like a postcode".
          render(OUTCODE_RE.test(raw) ? 'partial' : 'error');
          return;
        }

        var displayPostcode = (fullMatch[1] + ' ' + fullMatch[2]).toUpperCase();
        var url = 'https://api.postcodes.io/postcodes/' + encodeURIComponent(displayPostcode);

        setBusy(true);
        try {
          var res = await fetch(url);
          if (res.status === 404) {
            render('notfound');
            return;
          }
          if (!res.ok) {
            render('network');
            return;
          }
          var data = await res.json();
          var r = data && data.result;
          if (!r || typeof r.latitude !== 'number' || typeof r.longitude !== 'number') {
            render('notfound');
            return;
          }

          var miles = milesBetween(
            repairOrigin.lat, repairOrigin.lon,
            r.latitude, r.longitude
          );

          render(miles <= repairRadiusMiles ? 'covered' : 'outside', {
            postcode: r.postcode || r.outcode || displayPostcode,
            miles: miles,
          });
        } catch (err) {
          render('network');
        } finally {
          setBusy(false);
        }
      });
    })();
  </script>

  <style>
    .postcode-check {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      max-width: 480px;
      margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    }

    .postcode-check-input {
      flex: 1 1 220px;
      min-width: 0;
      padding: 0 1rem;
      min-height: 52px;
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      background-color: var(--color-bg-white);
      color: var(--color-text-dark);
      border: 2px solid var(--color-text-dark);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      transition: border-color var(--transition), box-shadow var(--transition);
    }

    .postcode-check-input::placeholder {
      color: var(--color-text-muted-dark);
      text-transform: none;
      letter-spacing: 0;
    }

    .postcode-check-input:focus {
      outline: none;
      border-color: var(--color-accent);
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(255, 45, 45, 0.18);
    }

    .postcode-check-submit {
      flex: 0 0 auto;
    }

    .postcode-check-result {
      max-width: 560px;
      margin: 1.75rem auto 0;
      padding: 1.5rem 1.4rem;
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      text-align: left;
    }

    .postcode-check-result[hidden] {
      display: none;
    }

    .postcode-check-result--covered {
      background-color: var(--color-bg-white);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
      border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
      text-align: center;
    }

    .postcode-check-result--outside {
      background-color: var(--color-bg-white);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
      border-left: 4px solid var(--color-text-dark);
    }

    .postcode-check-result--error {
      background-color: rgba(255, 45, 45, 0.06);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 45, 45, 0.25);
      text-align: center;
    }

    .postcode-check-headline {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.4vw, 1.55rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
      color: var(--color-text-dark);
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      line-height: 1.25;
    }

    .postcode-check-headline--error {
      color: var(--color-accent-dark);
      margin: 0;
    }

    .postcode-check-sub {
      color: var(--color-text-muted-dark);
      font-size: 0.97rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
    }

    .postcode-check-result--outside .postcode-check-sub:last-child,
    .postcode-check-result--covered .postcode-check-cta + * {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .postcode-check-cta {
      margin-top: 0.25rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 480px) {
      .postcode-check {
        flex-direction: column;
      }
      .postcode-check-input,
      .postcode-check-submit {
        flex: 0 0 auto;
        width: 100%;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
